# Conventional Commits

Use the format: `<type>(<scope>): <description>`

Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `perf`, `style`, `test`, `docs`, `build`, `ops`, `chore`

Scope is optional. Use imperative present tense ("add" not "added"). No period at end.

Examples:
- `feat(api): add identity verification endpoint`
- `fix(auth): handle expired Keycloak tokens`
- `test: add coverage for donation flow`

Breaking changes: Add `!` before colon and document in footer: `BREAKING CHANGE: description`

See https://www.conventionalcommits.org/ for full specification.
